contentheadline.headline: List of NATO reporting names for air-to-air missiles

contentrichtext.text: [[NATO reporting name]] for '''AA''' series [[air-to-air missile]]s, with [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] designations: * [[Kaliningrad K-5|AA-1]] "Alkali" (Kaliningrad K-5) * [[Vympel K-13|AA-2]] "Atoll" (Vympel K-13) * [[Kaliningrad K-8|AA-3]] "Anab" (Kaliningrad K-8) * [[Raduga K-9|AA-4]] "Awl" (Raduga K-9) * [[Bisnovat R-4|AA-5]] "Ash" (Bisnovat R-4) * [[Bisnovat R-40|AA-6]] "Acrid" (Bisnovat R-40) * [[Vympel R-23|AA-7]] "Apex" (Vympel R-23) * [[Molniya R-60|AA-8]] "Aphid" (Molniya R-60) * [[Vympel R-33|AA-9]] "Amos" (Vympel R-33) * [[Vympel R-27|AA-10]] "Alamo" (Vympel R-27) * [[Vympel R-73|AA-11]] "Archer" (Vympel R-73) * [[Vympel R-77|AA-12]] "Adder" (Vympel R-77) * [[Vympel R-37|AA-X-13]] "Arrow" (Vympel R-37) * - none - [[Novator K-100]] (was KS-172, R-172 etc.) ''See also'': [[NATO reporting name]] {{Russian and Soviet missiles|AAM}} [[Category:Lists of NATO reporting names|air-to-air missiles]] [[Category:Cold War air-to-air missiles of the Soviet Union]]
